cs.AR, cs.DB, cs.DC, cs.SE, cs.PF

Reasoning: 
- cs.AR (Architecture): The paper focuses on characterizing the micro-architectural behaviors of big data analytics workloads on modern processors, which falls under the domain of computer architecture. 
- cs.DB (Databases): Big data analytics applications deal with large volumes of data, and the paper investigates the impacts of these workloads on data center computer systems, which suggests a connection to the databases sub-category. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): Big data analytics workloads often require distributed and parallel computing, and the paper aims to understand their behaviors on modern processors, which aligns with the distributed, parallel, and cluster computing sub-category. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper also investigates the impacts of the big data software stack on application behaviors, which suggests a connection to the software engineering sub-category. 
- cs.PF (Performance): The paper aims to improve the performance of data center computer systems by understanding the behaviors of big data analytics workloads, which falls under the performance sub-category.
